HEADWORD: Evolutility
<hw>Ev`o*lu*til"i*ty</hw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧v`⟦osl⟧*l⟦usl⟧*t⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Evolution</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The faculty
possessed by all substances capable of self-nourishment of manifesting
the nutritive acts by changes of form, of volume, or of structure.</def>
<rj><au>Syd. Soc. Lex.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

